---
description: "Dockerfile/Dockerignore creation rules for layer/function image building in Python, Ruby, Node. Applies to Dockerfile and .dockerignore in any function/layer dir."
globs: "*/Dockerfile,*/.dockerignore"
alwaysApply: true
---
- Must include variant of buildx/build or `docker build` with `--platform=linux/amd64`
- Prohibit node_modules/dist/target/vendor/build in .dockerignore
- Must mount AWS creds via --secret if using provider build
- For Python, install requirements.txt to /build/python; for Ruby, handle vendor/bundle, for Node, expect node_modules/
